# Project Architecture

This project is an Expo Router + React Native app with feature-first source organization.

## Folder Responsibilities

- `app/`: route files, layouts, and screen entry points only
- `src/features/`: feature-specific UI and screen logic
- `src/components/`: shared presentation components
- `src/appState/`: app-level state stores
- `src/domain/`: business rules, guards, resolvers, capabilities
- `src/services/`: APIs, SDKs, analytics, notifications, and native integrations
- `src/hooks/`: reusable hooks
- `src/utils/`: pure helpers and low-level utilities
- `src/theme/`: colors, typography, brand tokens, strings, gradients, and shared visual language
- `supabase/functions/`: edge functions
- `supabase/migrations/`: database schema changes
- `__tests__/`: unit and regression tests

## Architecture Rules

- Keep route files thin. If route logic grows, move it into `src/features`.
- Put reusable business logic in `src/domain` rather than embedding it in UI files.
- Put external integration code in `src/services`.
- Prefer shared components in `src/components` only when they are used across features.
- Keep one-off feature UI inside its feature folder.
- Avoid mixing theme token definitions into feature files.
- Prefer pure helpers in `src/utils` for transform-style logic with no UI dependency.

## Agent Ownership

- Codex Lead: planning, architecture, integration, verification
- Cursor UI Agent: `app/**`, `src/features/**`, `src/components/**`
- Logic Agent: `src/domain/**`, `src/services/**`, `src/appState/**`, `src/hooks/**`, `src/utils/**`
- Theme Agent: `src/theme/**`, `global.css`
- Backend Agent: `supabase/**`
- Test Agent: `__tests__/**`

When a task crosses ownership areas, define the contract first and then split implementation by file boundary.
